('ChurchSantiCelsoEGiulianoRome', '<p class=\"justify\">Chiesa dei Santi Celso e Giuliano<br>12 Vicolo del Curato<br><br>Some relics of Saint Cornelius (d. 253) were transferred to this church in the 18th century. These relics are located in an urn to the right of the entrance.</p>', '', '', '', '', ''),
('ChurchstsMarcellinusPeter', '<p class=\"justify\">Chiesa dei Santi Marcellino e Pietro<br>Via Merulana 162<br><br>Relics of Saints Marcellinus and Peter (d. 304) are preserved within the main altar of this church. Typically on their feast day these relics are brought out and exposed for public veneration.*Above the main altar is a large painting depicting their martyrdom.</p>', '', '', '', '', ''),
